1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,500
The story of Arthur the Rat. Once upon a time, there was a young rat who couldn't make up his mind.

2
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:13,000
Whenever the other rats asked him if he would like to come out hunting with them,

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,500
he would answer in a hoarse voice, I don't know.

4
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:24,000
And when they said, would you rather stay inside, he would say yes or no either.

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,000
He'd always shake making a choice.

6
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,000
One fine day, his Aunt Josephine said to him,

7
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:37,000
now look here, no one will ever care for you if you carry on like this.

8
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:41,000
You have no more mind of your own than a greasy old blade of grass.

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
The young rat coughed and looked quiet as usual, but said nothing.

10
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Don't you think so, said his aunt, stamping her foot,

11
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:54,000
for she couldn't bear to see the young rat so cold-blooded.

12
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:00,000
I don't know, was all he ever answered, and then he walked off to think.

13
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:09,000
for an hour or more. Rather, he would stay in his hole in the ground or go out into the loft.

14
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:18,000
One night the rats heard a loud noise in the loft. It was a very dreary old place. The roof let the rain come down,

15
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:26,000
come washing in. The beams and the rafters had all rotted through, so the whole thing was quite unsafe.

16
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:35,000
At last, one of the joists gave way, and the beams fell with one edge on the floor.

17
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:45,000
The walls shook, the cupola fell off, and all the rats' hair stood on end with fear and horror.

18
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:54,000
This won't do, said the leader. We can't stay cooped up here any longer, so they sent out scouts to search for a new home.

19
00:01:54,000 --> 00:02:00,000
A little later on that evening, the scouts came back and said they had found an old-fashioned horse barn.

20
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
where there would be room for all of them. The leader gave the order at once,

21
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:11,000
come you following in, and the rats crawled out of the hole right away and stood on the floor in a long line.

22
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Just then the old rat caught sight of young Arthur. That was the name of the shaker.

23
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:24,000
He wasn't in the line, and he wasn't exactly outside it. He stood just by it.

24
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Come on, get in line, growled the old rat coarsely. Of course you're coming too.

25
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:41,000
I don't know, said Arthur calmly. Why the idea of it. You don't think it's safe here anymore, do you?

26
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:48,000
I'm not certain, said Arthur undaunted. The roof may not fall down yet.

27
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Well, said the old rat, you can't wait for you to join us.

28
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Then he turned to the other and shot it right about the face, marked.

29
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
And the long line marched out.

30
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:06,239
born while a young rat watched him. I think I'll go tomorrow, he said to himself, but then again

31
00:03:06,239 --> 00:03:14,560
perhaps I won't. It's so nice and snug here. I guess I'll go back to my hole under the log for a while

32
00:03:15,359 --> 00:03:22,559
just to make up my mind. But during the night there is a big crash. Down came beams, rafters,

33
00:03:22,559 --> 00:03:29,360
joists, the whole business. Next morning it was a foggy day. Some men came to look over the damage.

34
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:35,040
It seemed odd to them that the old building was not haunted by rats. But at last one of them

35
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:40,720
happened to move aboard and he caught sight of a young rat, quite dead, half in and half

36
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:48,080
out of his hole. Thus the shirker got his due and there was no mourning for him.

